    {
      "id": 358706,
      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>The proton NMR spectrum of a compound with formula C<sub>6</sub>H<sub>5</sub>NCl<sub>2</sub> is shown. The normal carbon-13 and DEPT experimental results are tabulated. The infrared spectrum shows peaks at 3432 and 3313 cm<sup>–1</sup> and a series of medium-sized peaks between 1618 and 1466 cm<sup>–1</sup>. Draw the structure of this compound.</p>\n<table class=\"unnumbered\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"text-align:left;\"><b>Normal Carbon</b></th>\n<th style=\"text-align:left;\"><b>DEPT-135</b></th>\n<th style=\"text-align:left;\"><b>DEPT-90</b></th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align:left;\">118.0 ppm</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left;\">Positive</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left;\">Positive</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align:left;\">119.5</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left;\">No peak</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left;\">No peak</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align:left;\">128.0</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left;\">Positive</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left;\">Positive</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align:left;\">140.0</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left;\">No peak</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:left;\">No peak</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<img src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBa1lWIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--ca9da1e95b1e62d10237b2fd4097181095d9dfd4/OChem_15_EC_025.jpg\" alt=\"The 1 H N M R spectrum of C 6 H 5 N C l 2 shows peaks in parts per million at 4.4 (broad), 6.6 (triplet), and 7.3 (doublet).\">",
